Record  pattenr
Record Patterns allow direct extraction of data from record objects 
without manually calling getter methods.
Record is shortcut class.

Example:

record Person(String name, int age) {}

Equivalent old class:

class Person {

    String name;
    int age;

    Person(String name, int age) {
        this.name = name;
        this.age = age;
    }
}

==========
Now Record Pattern means:

directly extracting values from record object.
Without Record Pattern:
Person p = new Person("Adarsh", 25);

System.out.println(p.name());
System.out.println(p.age());

Need getter methods.

With Record Pattern:

Object obj = new Person("Adarsh", 25);

if (obj instanceof Person(String name, int age)) {

    System.out.println(name);
    System.out.println(age);
}



