2. Pattern Matching for Switch
"Switch in Java 21 can match by TYPE, not just value. You can also add conditions.
No casting needed — compiler handles it.

Example:

switch(obj) {
    case String s -> System.out.println("String value: " + s);
}


👉 No need of instanceof + casting


